                <p>7.3 We are updating, maintaining, changing, upgrading, adjusting, replacing and / or other actions on the Application, Service and / or System (or any part thereof) and for that we are not obligated to be responsible to anyone; and / or the Merchant dies or the company, business entity, legal entity or civil partnership that you represent is declared or filed for bankruptcy or liquidation or is in a condition of bankruptcy or liquidation. You hereby agree to set aside the provisions of Article 1266 paragraph (2) and (3) of the Civil Code so that the Terms and Conditions, Applications and / or Services can be terminated (either partially or completely, temporarily or permanently) in accordance with these Terms. and Provisions without the need for a decision or ruling from a court judge.</p>
                <p>7.4 If the Account or Account has ended or closed or if the Service or Application has ended or is terminated by us, if:</p>
                <p>At that time, there are still remaining Points in your Account or if there are no Transactions carried out in or through your Account for a period of 6 (six) consecutive months. The Merchant hereby grants us full irrevocable and unconditional power, right and authority with the right of substitution, for any time, without requiring prior notification to the Merchant and without prior Merchant approval, cutting or debiting the balance in the Merchant Account. to fulfill all Merchant payment obligations to us including but not limited to paying administrative fees for Account closure in an amount to be determined by us from time to time; and termination of Account, Service or Application due to a violation by the Merchant of one or more of the Terms and Conditions, then the remaining balance in the Account will entirely become the right of  '.$pt.' and the Merchant agrees and binds not to ask for returns, payments, replacements and / or compensation in any form to  '.$pt.', the Merchant agrees and binds himself to not take any action that can limit, inhibit and / or reduce one or more rights and / or our authority under these Terms and Conditions and applicable law. You can take points or remaining funds after the account is closed if you forget WD, the balance / funds can be taken at Foresta Business Loft 5 Unit 23, Lengkong Kulon, Pagedangan, Tangerang, '.$brand.' head office by reporting to Customer Service if there is no identification of a violation, and bringing Evidence in the form of original identity cards or KTP on Monday to Friday 10.00 WIB to 15.00 WIB.</p>
                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                <p>8. APPLICABLE LAWS AND DISPUTE SETTLEMENT</p>
                <p>These Terms and Conditions are governed and interpreted based on the laws of the Republic of Indonesia.</p>
                <p>8.1. All disputes or contradictions that arise in connection with or related to matters stipulated in the Terms and Conditions (as well as parts thereof), including disputes caused by the existence or conduct of an illegal act or a violation of one or more of these Terms and Conditions ( "Dispute") must be resolved in the following manner: either the Merchant or  '.$pt.' ("First Party") is required to provide written notification to the other party ("Second Party") regarding the occurrence of a Dispute ("Dispute Notification") . Disputes must be resolved by deliberation to reach a consensus within 90 (ninety) calendar days from the date of the Dispute Dispute Notification ("Deliberative Settlement Period"); a. If the dispute cannot be resolved by deliberation to reach a consensus until the end of the Deliberative Settlement Period, the First Party and the Second Party are obliged to jointly appoint a third party (&ldquo;Mediator&rdquo;) as the mediator to settle the Dispute and the appointment must be written in a jointly signed form by First Party and Second Party. The mediation process by a special Mediator for disputes between Parties in the Banking sector, resolved by the Parties to LAPSPI, namely the Indonesian Banking Dispute Resolution Alternative Institution as stipulated in the Financial Services Authority Regulation Number 1 / POJK.07 / 2014 concerning Consumer Protection in the Financial Services Sector, which was promulgated January 23, 2014 (State Gazette of the Republic of Indonesia Year 2014 Number 12, Supplement to State Gazette of the Republic of Indonesia Number 5499) and its amendments if any. The Merchant is obliged to bear all costs, fees and expenses that we have incurred or may pay in the context of dispute resolution (including but not limited to fees, fees and expenses for attending arbitration hearings and for preparing and submitting all defenses, lawsuits, demands, information , evidence, information and / or any documents in the framework of implementation or during the arbitration proceedings) until the arbitration award is final and binding; Unless required by law applies or requested based on a request, decision or official ruling issued, issued or made by a court or authorized government agency, during the Dispute settlement process as regulated above until a decision is valid, final and binding on the First Party and the Second Party, then the Party The First and the Second Party are obliged to keep all information related to the Dispute and its settlement process confidential and therefore it is prohibited to in any way inform, notify or announce to any party the existence of the Dispute or its settlement process including but not limited to the mass media (newspapers, television or other media. ) and / or social media. You hereby acknowledge and agree that all or part of the Merchant\'s right to use the Service, Application, Account and / or PIN may be terminated or deactivated by us at any time, temporarily or permanently.</p>
                <p>OTHER PROVISIONS For any problems related to Transactions, Services and / or Accounts, you can ask for assistance at or from our '.$brand.' Contact Center or User Service on number [+62 89 7889 7889]. You can also make a written complaint to us to the following email address [info@'.$brand.'.co.id] by including supporting evidence that we can receive for submitting the written complaint. All approvals, power, authority and / or rights that you grant to us in these Terms and Conditions cannot be terminated for any reason including the reasons as referred to in Articles 1813, 1814 and 1816 of the Civil Code as long as you are still use the Service or Application or still use and / or have an Account. You hereby release us from all claims in connection with the implementation of all our actions based on the power, authority and / or rights that you have given us in or based on the Terms and Conditions or the exercise of our rights or authority under the Terms and Conditions</p>',
